WEBVTT

00:03.294 --> 00:05.922
[mellow piano music]

00:06.005 --> 00:09.718
- This place
looks incredible, Logan.

00:09.801 --> 00:14.764
- Okay, don't hate me, but...

00:14.848 --> 00:17.225
But I need to reschedule
our trip this weekend.

00:17.308 --> 00:19.602
- I already took off work
on Friday.

00:19.686 --> 00:21.146
- I'm sorry.

00:21.229 --> 00:22.772
I just got invited

00:22.856 --> 00:24.983
to speak at an immigrant rights
rally on Saturday.

00:25.066 --> 00:27.444
- Next weekend,
we have dinner at the Rubins.

00:27.527 --> 00:29.612
We can't cancel that.

00:29.696 --> 00:34.242
- Well, I know we shouldn't,
but what if we did?

00:34.325 --> 00:36.661
Cancelling's all the rage
these days.

00:36.745 --> 00:39.748
- Oh, love in the time
of cancel culture?

00:39.831 --> 00:43.418
- I'm just saying that anything
or anyone can be cancelled.

00:43.501 --> 00:45.462
[glass shatters]
- [gasps]

00:45.545 --> 00:47.130
- Stay there.

00:47.213 --> 00:50.133
[ominous music]

00:50.216 --> 00:52.010
♪ ♪

00:52.093 --> 00:53.970
It's a brick.
You okay?

00:54.053 --> 00:57.098
- We can't live like this.
- Call 911.

00:59.392 --> 01:00.518
- Wait, where are you going?

01:00.602 --> 01:02.520
- I'm just gonna talk to them.

01:02.604 --> 01:08.860
♪ ♪

01:08.943 --> 01:10.695
- Logan, don't!

01:11.905 --> 01:13.656
- [grunts]

01:13.740 --> 01:17.535
- [gasps, screams]

01:17.619 --> 01:20.663
[sobbing]

01:22.457 --> 01:25.376
[tense music]

01:25.460 --> 01:26.628
♪ ♪

01:26.711 --> 01:28.171
- Yeah, tonight's
a little gallery actually.

01:28.254 --> 01:30.340
- Thanks a lot.
- Can I help you, sir?

01:30.423 --> 01:32.050
- Tiff, you want
anything to eat?

01:32.133 --> 01:35.345
Sandwich, chips?
- No, the soda's fine, thanks.

01:35.428 --> 01:38.348
[soft music playing]

01:38.431 --> 01:39.891
♪ ♪

01:39.974 --> 01:43.353
- Tiffany Wallace?

01:43.436 --> 01:45.355
- Jemila.
[chuckles]

01:45.438 --> 01:47.357
It's been a long time.
It's good to see your face.

01:47.440 --> 01:49.567
- I thought you moved away.

01:49.651 --> 01:51.861
- I did, but I'm back.

01:52.821 --> 01:56.699
- You still a cop?
- FBI.

01:56.783 --> 01:58.326
This is actually
my partner Stuart.

01:58.409 --> 02:00.328
- Hey.
- Stuart, this is Jemila.

02:00.411 --> 02:01.996
We grew up together
in Bed-Stuy.

02:02.080 --> 02:04.040
- We used to be friends...

02:04.123 --> 02:06.459
till she put my brother away
for ten years.

02:07.168 --> 02:08.545
- He was dealing
to high school kids.

02:08.628 --> 02:09.879
I was doing my job.

02:09.963 --> 02:11.881
- Hm, that's the problem
right there.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.967
You got the wrong job.

02:15.218 --> 02:18.137
[soft dramatic music]

02:18.221 --> 02:21.391
♪ ♪

02:21.474 --> 02:22.725
- You good?

02:22.809 --> 02:25.061
- Yeah,
comes with the territory.

02:25.144 --> 02:28.481
[cell phone rings]

02:29.482 --> 02:30.984
- We gotta go.

02:33.152 --> 02:35.572
- 15 minutes ago,
Congressman Logan Reed

02:35.655 --> 02:40.076
was shot and killed
at his home in Scarsdale.

02:40.159 --> 02:41.744
Now, as most of you know,
Logan Reed

02:41.828 --> 02:43.746
was a rising star
in the Democratic Party,

02:43.830 --> 02:45.039
a former prosecutor.

02:45.123 --> 02:46.791
He rose to national prominence
last summer

02:46.875 --> 02:48.877
during all of
the racial unrest.

02:48.960 --> 02:51.129
Love him or hate him,
he was one of the most

02:51.212 --> 02:53.423
talked about politicians
in the country.

02:53.506 --> 02:55.550
- The story just broke online,
so the entire country's

02:55.633 --> 02:58.219
about to start asking if this
was politically motivated.

02:58.303 --> 02:59.596
We need answers and fast.

02:59.679 --> 03:01.264
- Let's get some, people.
Go to work.

03:01.347 --> 03:02.557
Now, Reed's
biggest campaign issues

03:02.640 --> 03:03.933
were racial justice
and police reform.

03:04.017 --> 03:05.768
He had a lot
of impassioned enemies,

03:05.852 --> 03:07.770
which means these days
a nonstop supply

03:07.854 --> 03:08.897
of death threats and hate mail,

03:08.980 --> 03:10.565
so let's scour
through all of it.

03:10.648 --> 03:11.983
Let's flag
everything high risk

03:12.066 --> 03:13.234
and ID any suspects

03:13.318 --> 03:16.237
within a striking distance
of the city, yep?

03:16.321 --> 03:17.739
- Anything from
the crime scene yet?

03:17.822 --> 03:19.198
- Maggie and OA just got there.

03:19.282 --> 03:20.825
Scola and Tiffany
are minutes away.

03:20.909 --> 03:22.619
- All right,
regular updates on all fronts.

03:22.702 --> 03:24.454
This story
is going to move and fast.

03:24.537 --> 03:25.914
We have to stay
one step ahead of it.

03:25.997 --> 03:27.790
- Yes, ma'am.

03:27.874 --> 03:29.959
- [sighs]

03:30.043 --> 03:32.462
- I'll have to arrange you
at about 60 feet.

03:32.545 --> 03:35.840
[police radio chatter]

03:35.924 --> 03:38.134
[person shouting indistinctly]

03:38.217 --> 03:40.136
- What do we know so far?
- Not enough.

03:40.219 --> 03:41.721
All these neighbors,
not one eyewitness.

03:41.804 --> 03:42.931
- And no security cameras
in the suburbs,

03:43.014 --> 03:44.349
so we're flying blind out here.

03:44.432 --> 03:45.808
- In a neighborhood like this,
there's gotta be

03:45.892 --> 03:46.851
doorbell cameras
in every house.

03:46.935 --> 03:49.145
- True,
but the Reeds' is broken,

03:49.228 --> 03:50.647
and there's no hits
on the neighbors' yet.

03:50.730 --> 03:52.649
Scarsdale PD's
still canvassing.

03:52.732 --> 03:53.983
- Reed was having dinner
with his wife

03:54.067 --> 03:55.193
when someone threw
a garden brick

03:55.276 --> 03:56.235
through the side window.

03:56.319 --> 03:58.488
He was shot the second
he opened the front door.

03:58.571 --> 04:00.114
- We're gonna go speak
with his wife now.

04:00.198 --> 04:01.491
- We'll take a look
at the window.

04:01.574 --> 04:02.992
- Meet back here in ten.

04:03.076 --> 04:04.661
♪ ♪

04:04.744 --> 04:05.954
- Yep, close it up.

04:06.037 --> 04:07.705
- Out of camera range,

04:07.789 --> 04:09.624
trees and bushes
providing cover.

04:09.707 --> 04:11.209
- Yeah, the killer was smart.

04:11.292 --> 04:13.169
Could have waited hours
for the perfect moment.

04:13.252 --> 04:15.171
- Yeah, copy that.

04:15.254 --> 04:17.507
- Canvass just turned up
a witness one block over.

04:17.590 --> 04:19.467
Lady getting her mail
saw a stranger

04:19.550 --> 04:21.469
come out of a backyard
wearing a black hoodie.

04:21.552 --> 04:23.513
- Where was that?
- Six houses that way.

04:23.596 --> 04:26.182
- She give a description?
- Just the hoodie.

04:26.265 --> 04:27.475
- Got it, thanks.

04:28.935 --> 04:30.478
So the shooter
disguised his identity

04:30.561 --> 04:31.854
and avoided cameras
by moving

04:31.938 --> 04:33.231
through backyards.

04:35.274 --> 04:37.068
- We got lots
of death threats,

04:37.151 --> 04:40.863
but I never thought
it would actually happen.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.700
It was just background noise.

04:43.783 --> 04:45.660
- Any of those threats
stick out?

04:45.743 --> 04:47.286
Anything seem like
an escalation?

04:52.166 --> 04:54.335
- It's okay.
I know this must be hard.

04:54.419 --> 04:55.878
You can take your time.

04:55.962 --> 04:58.006
- It's not that.
It's just...

04:59.465 --> 05:01.592
One thing does stand out,
but I don't...

05:03.553 --> 05:05.596
I don't want to give
the wrong impression.

05:06.931 --> 05:10.059
- You can't say
the wrong thing here.

05:11.561 --> 05:13.354
- There was a protest
at our house last week

05:13.438 --> 05:17.233
that got loud and scary.

05:17.316 --> 05:19.110
They broke our doorbell camera,

05:19.193 --> 05:20.737
and then someone threw
a brick through the window

05:20.820 --> 05:22.405
just like tonight.

05:22.488 --> 05:23.865
- Did you see
who threw the brick

05:23.948 --> 05:25.450
or get any pictures
of the protestors?

05:25.533 --> 05:27.785
- No, Logan wouldn't
let me outside.

05:27.869 --> 05:28.911
It was just...

05:30.496 --> 05:31.622
A little surprising.

05:32.999 --> 05:34.542
- Surprising how?

05:34.625 --> 05:37.462
- As you know, Logan...

05:37.545 --> 05:39.505
was a champion
for racial equality.

05:41.674 --> 05:43.926
But this crowd
was mostly Black.

05:46.262 --> 05:46.971
I know.

05:47.055 --> 05:49.432
I sound terrible
even saying it.

05:49.515 --> 05:51.601
- Did you call the police?

05:51.684 --> 05:52.727
- I wanted to, but he said

05:52.810 --> 05:55.313
it would only
inflame the situation.

05:55.396 --> 05:58.566
♪ ♪

05:58.649 --> 06:00.151
- All right, folks,
here's the question--

06:00.234 --> 06:03.321
how did a progressive ally
like Logan Reed

06:03.404 --> 06:06.699
end up in the crosshairs
of a minority protest group?

06:06.783 --> 06:08.409
- Well, the protest
at Reed's house

06:08.493 --> 06:10.453
was organized by Damian Thomas,

06:10.536 --> 06:12.789
a community activist
who lives in Reed's district,

06:12.872 --> 06:14.582
but he despises him.

06:14.665 --> 06:16.626
Called him
"the worst kind of racist,

06:16.709 --> 06:17.794
"a white liberal hypocrite

06:17.877 --> 06:19.587
"who co-opted
the Civil Rights Movement

06:19.670 --> 06:22.256
for his personal gain."
- That's pretty harsh.

06:22.340 --> 06:24.425
Next question is
why did Thomas feel this way?

06:24.509 --> 06:25.593
- Well, before he ran
for Congress,

06:25.676 --> 06:28.471
Reed was a prosecutor
known for being tough on crime.

06:28.554 --> 06:30.098
- Right, so Thomas thought
he was a hypocrite.

06:30.181 --> 06:31.974
One minute, he's putting
young Black men in prison,

06:32.058 --> 06:33.643
the next,
he's out on the streets

06:33.726 --> 06:35.311
protesting
with Black activists.

06:35.394 --> 06:37.021
- And he was preaching
all his newfound wokeness

06:37.105 --> 06:39.107
from his big-ass pad
in the suburbs.

06:39.190 --> 06:40.483
- And that.

06:40.566 --> 06:42.527
But would Thomas Reed
really kill over all this?

06:42.610 --> 06:45.488
- According
to Thomas himself, yes.

06:45.571 --> 06:48.991
- Logan Reed is a hypocrite
and a predator

06:49.075 --> 06:50.910
who needs to disappear.
- Hey.

06:50.993 --> 06:52.620
Punch into
his waistband there.

06:52.703 --> 06:54.163
- You can't play
both sides, Reed!

06:54.247 --> 06:55.289
[people chanting]
Reed must go!

06:55.373 --> 06:57.667
Reed must go!
Reed must go!

06:57.750 --> 06:59.502
- Looks like a .38.

06:59.585 --> 07:00.962
- Same caliber
used to kill Reed.

07:01.045 --> 07:02.505
I want to locate this guy now.

07:02.588 --> 07:04.799
- Okay, he's got
an apartment in Bushwick

07:04.882 --> 07:06.676
and a nonprofit office
in Crown Heights.

07:06.759 --> 07:08.219
- Okay, coordinate
with Maggie and OA.

07:08.302 --> 07:09.679
I want a team
in both locations.

07:09.762 --> 07:10.972
- Actually, Jubal...
- Yeah?

07:11.055 --> 07:12.890
- Social media says
Thomas is hosting a rally

07:12.974 --> 07:14.392
this morning
outside City Hall Park.

07:14.475 --> 07:16.727
He should be there for
at least another half an hour.

07:16.811 --> 07:19.313
- Okay, do that.
- Jubal.

07:19.397 --> 07:21.149
Guys, quick thought.

07:21.232 --> 07:22.150
- Homeland Security
have something?

07:22.233 --> 07:23.359
- Unofficially, yes.

07:23.442 --> 07:25.194
We've got Thomas
on a watchlist.

07:25.278 --> 07:27.363
You want his email, text,
and call history,

07:27.446 --> 07:29.031
it's yours
provided your data source

07:29.115 --> 07:30.324
stays off of any reports.

07:30.408 --> 07:33.870
- What did he do to get himself
on an unofficial watchlist?

07:33.953 --> 07:35.788
- He was arrested
three times last summer

07:35.872 --> 07:37.540
during the police reform
demonstrations.

07:37.623 --> 07:40.626
- Violent offenses?
- Curfew violations.

07:41.794 --> 07:43.212
- Curfew violations?

07:44.505 --> 07:46.424
So he stayed out
past his bedtime

07:46.507 --> 07:47.884
and ended up
on a damn watchlist,

07:47.967 --> 07:49.385
is that it?

07:49.468 --> 07:52.722
- Uh, this type of surveillance
is standard procedure.

07:52.805 --> 07:54.348
- Yeah,
that's part of the problem.

07:54.432 --> 07:55.558
- Yeah, look,
if there's any question

07:55.641 --> 07:57.185
about the legality
of the intel,

07:57.268 --> 07:58.895
we'll just build our case
another way.

07:58.978 --> 08:01.439
This investigation's
just too important.

08:01.522 --> 08:05.193
- Yeah, agreed,
let's not take any chances.

08:05.276 --> 08:06.611
Let's bring him in, yeah?

08:06.694 --> 08:13.743
♪ ♪

08:15.453 --> 08:16.787
- You know...

08:18.039 --> 08:19.165
It's one thing to wonder
if the government

08:19.248 --> 08:22.251
is spying on minority groups
they think are threatening.

08:22.335 --> 08:25.087
It's another thing
to know that they do.

08:25.171 --> 08:26.464
And then to work
with the people that do it,

08:26.547 --> 08:29.133
it makes me feel like
a damn hypocrite,

08:29.217 --> 08:31.594
like I'm fighting
the wrong fight.

08:31.677 --> 08:32.678
- Yeah.

08:33.721 --> 08:35.473
Hard to thread the needle
between where you work

08:35.556 --> 08:37.475
and who you really are...

08:40.394 --> 08:42.939
Especially these days.

08:43.022 --> 08:45.775
♪ ♪

08:45.858 --> 08:48.653
- Yeah, that's why
I stopped trying.

08:48.736 --> 08:52.448
[people chanting]
Police reform now!

08:52.531 --> 08:53.616
- That's him.
- All right.

08:53.699 --> 08:56.118
Let's get into place.
We'll grab him when he's done.

08:56.202 --> 08:58.329
- Black men
in this city make up

08:58.412 --> 09:02.583
a quarter of the population
and half of all arrests.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.335
That's not okay!

09:04.418 --> 09:07.004
Not if we're serious
about equality.

09:07.088 --> 09:09.715
That's why we're here today!

09:09.799 --> 09:12.343
That's why we're marching
on Saturday!

09:12.426 --> 09:15.346
[people chanting]
Police reform now!

09:18.057 --> 09:20.017
- I want to thank you all
for coming out.

09:20.101 --> 09:23.354
I'll see you on Saturday--
Bryant Park at noon!

09:23.437 --> 09:26.482
[cheers and applause]

09:31.612 --> 09:32.863
- Damian Thomas.

09:32.947 --> 09:35.157
- This is a peaceful gathering.
We have every right to be here.

09:35.241 --> 09:37.159
- FBI, we're gonna need you
to come with us.

09:37.243 --> 09:40.121
- Regarding what?
- The murder of Logan Reed.

09:41.205 --> 09:42.164
- That's ridiculous.

09:42.248 --> 09:43.332
- Turn around, put your hands
behind your back.

09:43.416 --> 09:44.250
- Maybe slapping on the cuffs
isn't the play right now.

09:44.333 --> 09:46.836
- Riding behind me,
he's wearing cuffs.

09:46.919 --> 09:48.254
- Let's just get him
to the car.

09:48.337 --> 09:49.463
- No, no,
get your hands off me!

09:49.547 --> 09:50.214
- That's it.

09:50.298 --> 09:51.299
Put your hands
behind your back.

09:51.382 --> 09:53.676
- Laila, bring the camera!

09:53.759 --> 09:54.927
- Dad, what the hell
is going on?

09:55.011 --> 09:57.013
- You need to back up, ma'am.
- Why are you arresting him?

09:57.096 --> 09:57.930
- We're not.

09:58.014 --> 09:59.181
We're just detaining him
for questioning.

09:59.265 --> 10:00.516
- Why are you arresting
my father?

10:00.599 --> 10:01.642
- Stand back now.

10:01.726 --> 10:02.810
- Why are you arresting
my father?

10:02.893 --> 10:04.854
- FBI, back up!
- You kidding me?

10:04.937 --> 10:05.855
You won't even
look me in the eye?

10:05.938 --> 10:07.398
- I'm looking right at you,

10:07.481 --> 10:09.025
and I'm telling you
to back down.

10:09.108 --> 10:12.695
- I hope it feels good, Sister,
selling out your people.

10:12.778 --> 10:14.196
- He didn't do nothing!

10:14.280 --> 10:17.074
- You don't know me.

10:17.158 --> 10:18.701
- Y'all crazy!
- Bullies!

10:18.784 --> 10:21.704
[people shouting indistinctly]

10:21.787 --> 10:25.041
♪ ♪

10:25.124 --> 10:28.002
- You think
I killed Logan Reed?

10:28.085 --> 10:30.755
- You stood outside his house
last week with a gun

10:30.838 --> 10:32.340
yelling that he needed
to disappear,

10:32.423 --> 10:34.675
so yeah.

10:34.759 --> 10:36.677
- I admit I got carried away
with that,

10:36.761 --> 10:39.597
but I didn't mean what I said.
I don't even own a gun.

10:39.680 --> 10:41.724
- All right,
let's try this again.

10:41.807 --> 10:44.560
Maybe this time
don't treat us like idiots.

10:44.644 --> 10:46.562
- [chuckles]
Come on, man.

10:46.645 --> 10:49.231
I took that gun
off a kid at the rally.

10:49.315 --> 10:52.526
He was a hothead.
I don't stand for violence.

10:52.610 --> 10:54.195
- Except for when
you're making death threats.

10:54.278 --> 10:55.321
- Or someone throws a brick

10:55.404 --> 10:56.530
through the congressman's
window.

10:56.614 --> 10:58.074
- The hothead did that.

10:58.157 --> 10:59.575
It's a good thing
I took away his gun.

10:59.658 --> 11:00.951
- You give it back to him?

11:01.035 --> 11:02.787
- I got rid of it
at a gun buyback.

11:02.870 --> 11:04.538
I got the receipt, if it helps.

11:04.622 --> 11:07.666
- Where were you at 7:00 p.m.
last night?

11:10.169 --> 11:12.588
- I know y'all got a job to do,

11:12.671 --> 11:15.257
but this story gets old.

11:15.341 --> 11:17.593
Rich white guy gets shot.

11:17.676 --> 11:21.514
Cops go nuts, start rounding up
innocent Black men.

11:21.597 --> 11:23.391
The FBI gets involved.
- Okay.

11:23.474 --> 11:25.726
A United States congressman
was murdered.

11:25.810 --> 11:27.728
This country
is at a tipping point.

11:27.812 --> 11:29.980
- And yet five miles away
in his own district,

11:30.064 --> 11:32.483
the murders of young, Black men
barely register,

11:32.566 --> 11:34.610
so forgive me if
I'm not shedding any tears

11:34.693 --> 11:36.737
for this two-faced politician.

11:36.821 --> 11:40.574
♪ ♪

11:40.658 --> 11:42.451
- Where were you at 7:00 p.m.?

11:42.535 --> 11:47.039
- Making sure my people are
fairly treated by the police.

11:47.915 --> 11:50.626
I was speaking
at a community action dinner.

11:50.709 --> 11:52.461
That's what I do.

11:52.545 --> 11:54.630
In fact, when you arrested me,
I was on my way

11:54.713 --> 11:57.007
to visit the mother
of a young, Black man

11:57.091 --> 11:59.927
who had been murdered
for no damned reason.

12:00.010 --> 12:02.638
This kid's
minding his own business.

12:02.721 --> 12:05.141
A brick gets thrown
through his window.

12:05.224 --> 12:07.935
He rushes outside,
gets shot twice.

12:08.018 --> 12:10.146
- When was that exactly?

12:10.229 --> 12:11.772
- Last night.

12:11.856 --> 12:13.315
- Do you know
the victim's name?

12:13.399 --> 12:16.861
- Of course I do--
Marcus Ervin.

12:20.698 --> 12:22.199
- Thomas' alibi checks out.

12:22.283 --> 12:23.701
Security footage
from the restaurant

12:23.784 --> 12:25.995
confirms that he was having
dinner when Reed was shot.

12:26.078 --> 12:28.456
- NYPD says Marcus Ervin
was shot last night

12:28.539 --> 12:30.374
in Brooklyn around 10:00 p.m.
while he was standing

12:30.458 --> 12:32.042
in the doorway
of his ground floor apartment

12:32.126 --> 12:33.961
after a rock came crashing
through his window.

12:34.044 --> 12:36.005
- Same MO as Reed.

12:36.088 --> 12:38.549
- They run the ballistics yet?
- It's the same gun.

12:38.632 --> 12:40.801
- All right, that's two murders
within three hours.

12:40.885 --> 12:42.011
- That we know of.

12:42.094 --> 12:43.846
We could be looking
at a killing spree.

12:43.929 --> 12:45.514
All right, go to Brooklyn now.

12:45.598 --> 12:48.350
[dramatic music]

12:48.434 --> 12:48.767
- [sighs]

12:54.148 --> 12:55.024
- Game faces, people!

12:55.107 --> 12:57.359
We now have two victims
of the same gunman

12:57.443 --> 12:58.694
who might not be done
shooting yet.

12:58.777 --> 12:59.904
Three hours after killing

12:59.987 --> 13:01.906
Congressman Reed
in the suburbs,

13:01.989 --> 13:03.324
our shooter resurfaced
in Brooklyn

13:03.407 --> 13:05.034
and killed this man,
Marcus Ervin.

13:05.117 --> 13:06.911
He's 20 years old.
He's a retail clerk.

13:06.994 --> 13:09.497
Lived with his mother,
was taking IT classes at night.

13:09.580 --> 13:11.540
The question is why--
either there's a connection

13:11.624 --> 13:13.167
between these two murders,

13:13.250 --> 13:14.877
or we have a madman
on the loose

13:14.960 --> 13:15.878
throwing rocks
through random windows

13:15.961 --> 13:17.421
and shooting whoever walks out.

13:17.505 --> 13:18.756
- If these two men
were targeted,

13:18.839 --> 13:20.049
they were not killed
for their differences.

13:20.132 --> 13:21.717
They were killed
for their similarities.

13:21.800 --> 13:23.511
What do these two men
have in common?

13:23.594 --> 13:25.054
- There's no luck
on the political front.

13:25.137 --> 13:26.388
I just talked
to Reed's chief of staff.

13:26.472 --> 13:27.765
She doesn't know Marcus,
but she put his name

13:27.848 --> 13:29.350
in the volunteer database,
and there's no record

13:29.433 --> 13:31.435
that he ever worked there.
- Same goes for Reed's wife.

13:31.519 --> 13:33.229
I mean, as far as she knows,
Reed never spent

13:33.312 --> 13:34.396
any time
in that part of Bushwick.

13:34.480 --> 13:35.898
- Okay, thanks, guys.

13:35.981 --> 13:37.149
Hey, Kelly, have your team
start scrubbing

13:37.233 --> 13:39.235
through videos from the area
surrounding both crime scenes

13:39.318 --> 13:40.402
and flag anything
that appears in both.

13:40.486 --> 13:41.403
- On it.

13:41.487 --> 13:43.405
- Ian, you guys run financials
on both victims.

13:43.489 --> 13:45.241
Look for any common patterns--
expenses, accounts.

13:45.324 --> 13:46.784
Let's get creative, folks!

13:46.867 --> 13:48.577
Our shooter might have plans
to strike again.

13:48.661 --> 13:50.329
Travel history,
online hangouts,

13:50.412 --> 13:51.580
common acquaintances.

13:51.664 --> 13:52.873
I don't know.
Surprise me.

13:52.957 --> 13:53.916
- You got anything
from Tiffany and Scola yet?

13:53.999 --> 13:56.460
- They're talking
to Marcus' mother as we speak.

13:56.544 --> 13:59.463
Maybe she knows something
we haven't seen from here.

13:59.547 --> 14:02.466
[soft dramatic music]

14:02.550 --> 14:03.801
- You're telling me
the same guy

14:03.884 --> 14:06.095
who killed a congressman
killed my son?

14:06.178 --> 14:08.389
- That's our working theory
at the moment.

14:08.472 --> 14:11.058
- So that's why y'all suddenly
give a damn--

14:11.141 --> 14:13.060
'cause a white congressman
is involved.

14:13.143 --> 14:14.937
- Ma'am, we're just trying
to find the man

14:15.020 --> 14:16.564
who shot your son.

14:17.565 --> 14:19.608
Can you think of anything
that might connect Marcus

14:19.692 --> 14:21.277
to Logan Reed?
- No.

14:21.360 --> 14:24.071
Marcus wasn't involved
in politics.

14:24.154 --> 14:25.573
- Have there been
recent threats,

14:25.656 --> 14:27.950
or did he have any enemies?
- Yeah.

14:28.033 --> 14:30.286
You're not gonna like it.

14:30.369 --> 14:33.581
He was a good kid.
Kept his head down.

14:33.664 --> 14:36.959
Did his work,
and I can tell you right now

14:37.042 --> 14:40.087
he wanted nothing
to do with the gangs.

14:40.170 --> 14:44.174
Only people who hated my son
were the local cops.

14:44.258 --> 14:46.093
- Excuse me?

14:46.176 --> 14:47.970
- Marcus didn't like
the way the police

14:48.053 --> 14:52.099
treated people around here,
so if they crossed the line,

14:52.182 --> 14:54.143
he'd let 'em hear it,

14:54.226 --> 14:57.813
and they crossed
plenty of lines.

14:57.896 --> 14:59.315
My opinion?

14:59.398 --> 15:03.861
Cops killed my son.

15:03.944 --> 15:06.363
- And do you have any evidence
to back that up?

15:06.447 --> 15:12.036
♪ ♪

15:12.119 --> 15:14.288
- Two days ago,
some off-duty cop

15:14.371 --> 15:16.790
jumped out
of an unmarked cop car

15:16.874 --> 15:19.001
and beat him senseless.

15:19.084 --> 15:21.837
♪ ♪

15:21.920 --> 15:24.006
- And did Marcus
go to the hospital?

15:24.089 --> 15:26.008
- He was too afraid.

15:26.091 --> 15:30.179
Cops said to keep
his mouth shut.

15:30.262 --> 15:32.014
- Did you take photos
of the injuries?

15:32.097 --> 15:34.350
♪ ♪

15:34.433 --> 15:36.518
If you can tell us
where the attack took place,

15:36.602 --> 15:39.021
we'll talk to the NYPD
and get you some answers.

15:39.104 --> 15:40.439
- [scoffs]

15:40.522 --> 15:43.108
I won't hold my breath.

15:43.192 --> 15:45.903
♪ ♪

15:45.986 --> 15:49.615
- We're gonna find the person
responsible for Marcus' death,

15:49.698 --> 15:50.991
so please,

15:51.075 --> 15:53.827
can you tell us exactly
where Marcus was attacked?

15:53.911 --> 15:57.206
♪ ♪

15:57.289 --> 15:59.541
- The intersection of Irving
and Dekalb in Bushwick.

15:59.625 --> 16:01.543
We have video of the attack.
- Oh, great.

16:01.627 --> 16:03.379
- Happened
at 4:17 p.m. Tuesday.

16:03.462 --> 16:06.006
- All right, eyes up, people!
Let's check it out.

16:06.090 --> 16:09.051
- That is Marcus Ervin
stepping off the curb,

16:09.134 --> 16:12.763
and I presume that is the cop
his mother was talking about.

16:12.846 --> 16:14.348
- He could have killed him
right here.

16:14.431 --> 16:15.724
Why wait a few days?
- Mm.

16:15.808 --> 16:17.226
Are we gonna be able
to identify the attacker?

16:17.309 --> 16:18.894
- No, it's too grainy
for an ID,

16:18.977 --> 16:21.105
but we can read
the license plate.

16:21.188 --> 16:23.399
- Yep, got it.
Car is owned by a Cody McCowan.

16:23.482 --> 16:25.859
He lives in Flatbush.
- He with the NYPD?

16:25.943 --> 16:27.611
- No, definitely not.

16:27.695 --> 16:30.239
- But Marcus' mom
said a cop beat him up.

16:30.322 --> 16:31.740
- Well, his mother was wrong.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.033
McCowan has got three priors,

16:33.117 --> 16:35.411
all for assault,
no convictions.

16:35.494 --> 16:38.914
He's got an outstanding warrant
for aggravated battery.

16:38.997 --> 16:41.542
- Hate Crimes has
a pretty big file on this guy.

16:41.625 --> 16:43.293
He used to own
a sporting goods shop.

16:43.377 --> 16:44.420
Went out of business,

16:44.503 --> 16:46.171
channeled his anger
into politics,

16:46.255 --> 16:47.423
started a local group

16:47.506 --> 16:50.342
called the Brooklyn Blockade--
BKB--

16:50.426 --> 16:53.095
fighting neighborhood change
with intimidation and violence.

16:53.178 --> 16:54.179
- Neighborhood change,

16:54.263 --> 16:56.223
meaning he wants
to keep his neighborhood white.

16:56.306 --> 16:58.100
But why attack Marcus?
Why'd he hate him so much?

16:58.183 --> 17:00.269
- I'm not sure yet.
- There's gotta be a reason.

17:00.352 --> 17:01.645
Let's find it.
- Hey.

17:01.729 --> 17:03.272
I just found a connection.

17:03.355 --> 17:05.774
Looks like Cody hated
Congressman Reed too.

17:05.858 --> 17:07.484
- What?
What are you talking about?

17:07.568 --> 17:09.111
- He made a bunch of
online threats against him

17:09.194 --> 17:10.279
over the past few months.

17:10.362 --> 17:13.907
He blamed politicians like Reed
for ruining his community.

17:13.991 --> 17:16.535
- Hey, McCowan's got six guns
registered to his name.

17:16.618 --> 17:19.204
- One of 'em a .38?
- Smith & Wesson 640.

17:19.288 --> 17:21.582
- All right, folks, we got
a new leader in the clubhouse!

17:21.665 --> 17:23.959
Cody McCowan,
he assaulted Marcus Ervin,

17:24.042 --> 17:25.502
he threatened Congressman Reed,

17:25.586 --> 17:27.921
and he has a gun
that matches the murder weapon.

17:28.005 --> 17:29.631
Let's get an address
and bring him in.

17:29.715 --> 17:33.177
♪ ♪

17:33.260 --> 17:36.847
- Cody McCowan on any
of your unofficial watchlists?

17:36.930 --> 17:39.641
- No.
- Come on.

17:39.725 --> 17:42.519
What's a white boy gotta do
to get some love from the DHS?

17:42.603 --> 17:45.439
- [sighs]
Look, I don't make the lists.

17:45.522 --> 17:47.858
- That is a weak excuse.

17:47.941 --> 17:50.027
- Just telling you
the way it is.

17:50.110 --> 17:51.987
- Yeah, well,
the way it is sucks.

17:52.070 --> 17:54.031
- You got a problem
with the rules,

17:54.114 --> 17:55.991
take it up
the chain of command.

17:56.074 --> 17:58.619
- Y'all have been hiding
behind that line for 100 years.

17:58.702 --> 18:00.496
- I don't appreciate
your attitude.

18:00.579 --> 18:01.997
- My attitude?
What does that mean?

18:02.080 --> 18:03.290
- What the hell
are you trying--

18:03.373 --> 18:05.000
- Okay, enough, enough.
We got work to do.

18:05.083 --> 18:10.339
♪ ♪

18:10.422 --> 18:12.007
- I got an address.
- Yeah?

18:12.090 --> 18:13.675
- Hate Crimes says
McCowan and the BKB

18:13.759 --> 18:16.512
hang out at a place
called Irish Haven in Brooklyn.

18:16.595 --> 18:17.679
Bar's owned
by Cody's mother Janine.

18:17.763 --> 18:18.931
- Okay, great,
call Maggie and OA.

18:19.014 --> 18:20.682
Get 'em over there now.

18:20.766 --> 18:25.896
♪ ♪

18:25.979 --> 18:27.272
Tiffany.

18:32.444 --> 18:35.030
So I get it.

18:35.114 --> 18:38.575
You disagree
with what DHS is doing,

18:38.659 --> 18:41.829
but you were
out of line back there.

18:41.912 --> 18:43.247
- Excuse me?

18:43.330 --> 18:45.499
- Look, this place, the JOC,

18:45.582 --> 18:48.210
it only works if we're a team,
you know?

18:48.293 --> 18:51.547
If we play together in harmony.

18:53.799 --> 18:56.218
End of the day,
we got a job to do.

18:56.301 --> 18:58.846
It's simple as that.

19:02.099 --> 19:03.559
Thanks.

19:08.146 --> 19:09.898
- Can I get another one,
please?

19:09.982 --> 19:12.609
And this time, try to make sure
this one's not so bubbly.

19:12.693 --> 19:15.195
- Can I help you?
- Cody McCowan, you know him?

19:15.279 --> 19:16.530
- Sorry, man.

19:16.613 --> 19:17.948
Cool vest, though.

19:18.031 --> 19:20.909
Those thing come with a helmet?
- [chuckles]

19:20.993 --> 19:22.411
- I'ma need you
to think really hard

19:22.494 --> 19:24.121
before you
open your mouth again.

19:24.204 --> 19:26.582
Cody McCowan,
where can I find him?

19:26.665 --> 19:29.960
- Keep in mind, you lie to us,
you're gonna go to prison.

19:30.043 --> 19:31.920
- What do you want
with Cody McCowan?

19:32.004 --> 19:33.463
- Who are you?

19:33.547 --> 19:37.259
- Janine McCowan.
Cody's my son.

19:37.342 --> 19:38.969
What'd he do,
run his mouth again?

19:39.052 --> 19:41.430
- Yes, he did, and we'd love
to talk to him about it.

19:41.513 --> 19:43.557
- Only reason he talks that way
is 'cause the cops

19:43.640 --> 19:45.601
are afraid to do
their damn job around here.

19:45.684 --> 19:47.102
Somebody's gotta step up.

19:47.185 --> 19:48.562
- The FBI is stepping up,

19:48.645 --> 19:51.565
which is why we need to speak
with him right now.

19:51.648 --> 19:53.275
[door opens]

19:53.358 --> 19:54.902
- Dude, get out of here.

19:54.985 --> 19:56.236
- Cody McCowan!

19:56.320 --> 19:57.446
[dramatic music]

19:57.529 --> 19:58.614
- FBI, stop!

19:58.697 --> 20:00.741
- Hey, it's a peaceful protest.
- Get out of my way.

20:00.824 --> 20:03.410
- [grunts]
- Don't leave this bar, okay?

20:03.493 --> 20:10.500
♪ ♪

20:14.046 --> 20:14.671
- He's gone.

20:21.720 --> 20:23.096
- Cody McCowan's
still at large.

20:23.180 --> 20:24.598
Last seen fleeing
the Irish Haven.

20:24.681 --> 20:25.807
- Street cam
is drawing a blank.

20:25.891 --> 20:27.142
He might've ducked
into a store front

20:27.225 --> 20:28.977
and out into a back alley.

20:29.061 --> 20:30.646
- Yeah, I'm scrubbing footage
from area security cameras.

20:30.729 --> 20:31.813
So far, nothing.

20:31.897 --> 20:33.315
- Did we get anything
from the BKB?

20:33.398 --> 20:35.484
- No, the guys we arrested
lawyered up right away.

20:35.567 --> 20:37.486
- And no one else
from the bar is talking.

20:37.569 --> 20:38.654
- I found something.

20:38.737 --> 20:41.448
The reason Cody McCowan
might have killed Marcus Ervin

20:41.531 --> 20:43.659
and Congressman Reed.

20:43.742 --> 20:45.786
This photo was taken
at a protest march last summer.

20:45.869 --> 20:47.329
The guy with the bat
is Cody McCowan's

20:47.412 --> 20:48.330
half brother Jack Powell.

20:48.413 --> 20:50.666
The guy he's assaulting,
that's Marcus Ervin.

20:50.749 --> 20:53.001
Marcus Ervin
testified against Powell

20:53.085 --> 20:55.212
who was convicted of ag assault
with a hate crime kicker.

20:55.295 --> 20:57.506
Got sentenced
to five years in prison.

20:57.589 --> 20:59.174
- Right, so Cody
was looking for payback.

20:59.257 --> 21:00.342
That makes sense,
but what does this photo

21:00.425 --> 21:01.718
have to do
with Congressman Reed?

21:01.802 --> 21:03.679
- Reed used it
in his campaign video.

21:03.762 --> 21:05.055
He kept showing it,
saying it was the sort

21:05.138 --> 21:08.266
of racism and violence
that he wanted to abolish.

21:08.350 --> 21:09.309
- Huh.
- Pulling it up now.

21:09.393 --> 21:12.187
- So Marcus Ervin's testimony
put Jack Powell,

21:12.270 --> 21:14.523
Cody's half brother,
behind bars,

21:14.606 --> 21:16.858
and Congressman Reed's campaign
made him the face

21:16.942 --> 21:19.695
of angry, white racism.
That sounds like motive to me.

21:19.778 --> 21:20.862
- Is Jack Powell
still in prison?

21:20.946 --> 21:24.157
- Yes, at Rikers, but he's
currently in the hospital wing.

21:24.241 --> 21:27.703
[dramatic music]

21:27.786 --> 21:33.875
♪ ♪

21:35.627 --> 21:37.045
- When did this happen?

21:37.129 --> 21:38.547
- Tuesday in the yard.

21:38.630 --> 21:40.048
He was known
for being a racist.

21:40.132 --> 21:42.300
He got beat down
by a Black gang.

21:42.384 --> 21:44.219
The guards stopped it
in under a minute,

21:44.302 --> 21:45.721
but the damage is already done.

21:45.804 --> 21:48.223
- How bad is it?
- Bad.

21:48.307 --> 21:50.392
Severe TBI,
might not ever wake up,

21:50.475 --> 21:53.103
and even if he does,
he's not gonna recover.

21:53.186 --> 21:55.397
[scoffs]

21:55.480 --> 21:57.524
- Jack's got an older brother,
Cody McCowan.

21:57.607 --> 21:59.443
- Yeah, guy's a piece of work.

21:59.526 --> 22:01.737
He's called me a dozen times
since the attack,

22:01.820 --> 22:03.363
threatening to sue.

22:03.447 --> 22:04.906
- Do you have his phone number?

22:04.990 --> 22:06.742
- In our records.
Why?

22:06.825 --> 22:09.453
- Cody's a suspect
in two recent homicides.

22:09.536 --> 22:11.246
- Both happened last night.

22:11.329 --> 22:12.706
There's a good chance
Jack's beat down

22:12.789 --> 22:14.708
was the catalyst.

22:14.791 --> 22:17.794
[monitor beeping]

22:19.004 --> 22:20.714
- Based on the Rikers
telephone record,

22:20.797 --> 22:22.632
Cody McCowan learned
of Jack's prison yard beating

22:22.716 --> 22:24.426
10:04 a.m. on Tuesday morning.

22:24.509 --> 22:27.929
Then six hours later, in what
seems like a direct response,

22:28.013 --> 22:29.014
beats Marcus in the street.

22:29.097 --> 22:31.641
Then, last night, both Marcus
and Congressman Reed

22:31.725 --> 22:33.226
are shot and killed.

22:33.310 --> 22:34.811
- Any luck tracking
Cody's phone?

22:34.895 --> 22:37.272
- Yeah, I just got up
on the new number.

22:37.355 --> 22:39.608
No location data,
but for the past two hours,

22:39.691 --> 22:40.984
it's been pinging off
the same three towers

22:41.068 --> 22:42.903
in Brooklyn putting him
somewhere within

22:42.986 --> 22:45.781
these ten square blocks.
- Okay, okay.

22:45.864 --> 22:48.241
We are looking
for an address in Flatbush.

22:48.325 --> 22:49.659
Does Cody have
any relatives there?

22:49.743 --> 22:51.078
Any friends from the BKB?

22:51.161 --> 22:52.913
Any references
on social media posts?

22:52.996 --> 22:53.914
Let's go.

22:53.997 --> 22:55.957
I want to be kicking in a door
in 20 minutes,

22:56.041 --> 22:58.794
and I need someone in here
to tell me exactly which one.

22:58.877 --> 23:00.629
- There's nothing useful
on his social media pages.

23:00.712 --> 23:01.963
It's all trolling
and hate speech.

23:02.047 --> 23:04.174
- Yeah, the BKB guys
we have addresses for

23:04.257 --> 23:06.301
all live closer to the bar.
- Got something, Jubal.

23:06.384 --> 23:07.803
- An address in Flatbush,
I hope.

23:07.886 --> 23:09.179
- McCowan's ex-wife
lists her permanent home

23:09.262 --> 23:11.306
in New Jersey
but still owns an apartment

23:11.389 --> 23:14.518
at 1565 Lynwood Place,
Flatbush.

23:14.601 --> 23:16.812
♪ ♪

23:16.895 --> 23:20.774
- That is right in the middle
of the three cell towers.

23:20.857 --> 23:23.777
[dramatic music]

23:23.860 --> 23:27.155
♪ ♪

23:27.239 --> 23:29.699
- Billy Joel,
you'll be home later.

23:29.783 --> 23:32.953
- Cody McCowan, FBI!

23:33.036 --> 23:39.793
♪ ♪

23:55.767 --> 24:02.774
♪ ♪

24:20.917 --> 24:22.627
- [grunts]

24:25.046 --> 24:28.633
- He's at 21st and Newkirk.
He's on the roof heading south.

24:28.717 --> 24:35.724
♪ ♪

24:39.853 --> 24:40.896
[tires screech]

24:43.148 --> 24:45.901
- FBI, stop!
Put your hands up.

24:45.984 --> 24:47.903
Higher!

24:47.986 --> 24:49.863
Turn away from me.

24:49.946 --> 24:56.953
♪ ♪

24:59.039 --> 25:00.707
- All these criminals
running in the streets,

25:00.790 --> 25:01.958
and what do you do?

25:02.042 --> 25:03.543
You arrest an innocent man.

25:03.627 --> 25:05.295
- If you're so innocent,
then why'd you run?

25:05.378 --> 25:07.380
- I got outstanding warrants,

25:07.464 --> 25:09.424
and I didn't feel like
surrendering just yet--

25:09.507 --> 25:10.675
more work to do,

25:10.759 --> 25:13.720
since the cops don't have the
guts to do their jobs anymore.

25:17.015 --> 25:19.059
- This your idea
of police work?

25:19.142 --> 25:21.728
- That's called payback.
- For what?

25:21.811 --> 25:23.271
- Race riots last summer.

25:23.355 --> 25:26.107
- Oh, you're referring
to the protests.

25:26.191 --> 25:28.276
- Looked more like riots to me.

25:28.360 --> 25:30.612
This punk Marcus
threw a brick

25:30.695 --> 25:33.114
through the window
of my mom's bar.

25:33.198 --> 25:34.574
Looters stormed inside,

25:34.658 --> 25:36.284
started destroying the place
like animals.

25:36.368 --> 25:38.328
Cops didn't do a damn thing
to stop it.

25:38.411 --> 25:39.454
- So that gives
your brother Jack

25:39.537 --> 25:40.914
the right to take
a bat to his head?

25:40.997 --> 25:42.457
- To save our mom's bar!

25:42.540 --> 25:46.253
It's called self-defense.
And the internet runs with it.

25:46.336 --> 25:48.463
All of a sudden,
we're evil racists.

25:48.546 --> 25:50.298
They started it, not us.

25:50.382 --> 25:51.800
We were minding
our own business,

25:51.883 --> 25:56.137
and then they started
protesting and looting.

25:56.221 --> 25:57.973
But my brother's the one
who got sent to prison,

25:58.056 --> 25:59.933
and now he's hooked up
to a feeding tube,

26:00.016 --> 26:02.519
so hell yeah,
I kicked that kid's ass.

26:02.602 --> 26:04.646
- Yean, but that wasn't enough.

26:04.729 --> 26:07.148
That's why you went
after Marcus again, right?

26:07.232 --> 26:08.858
But this time, you killed him.

26:08.942 --> 26:11.528
- Right after you killed
Congressman Reed?

26:11.611 --> 26:13.363
- What the hell
are you talking about?

26:13.446 --> 26:15.490
- Come on, Cody,
you said it yourself.

26:15.573 --> 26:17.659
Your brother got screwed.
You wanted revenge.

26:17.742 --> 26:20.829
- Yeah,
but I didn't kill anybody.

26:20.912 --> 26:22.289
[door buzzes, opens]

26:22.372 --> 26:24.332
- Hey, we need to talk.

26:24.416 --> 26:27.335
[soft dramatic music]

26:27.419 --> 26:30.380
♪ ♪

26:30.463 --> 26:32.007
- So Tiffany and Scola
just called.

26:32.090 --> 26:33.842
Damian Thomas,
the community activist

26:33.925 --> 26:35.218
who told us about
Marcus' murder,

26:35.302 --> 26:37.512
he was just killed
30 minutes ago.

26:37.595 --> 26:39.264
He was shot in the chest
after somebody

26:39.347 --> 26:41.016
threw a brick
through his office window.

26:41.099 --> 26:42.851
- Are we sure this is related?

26:42.934 --> 26:44.811
- ERT pulled a second slug
from the wall.

26:44.894 --> 26:46.187
Preliminary ballistics
are a match

26:46.271 --> 26:48.565
to the other two murders,
which means--

26:48.648 --> 26:49.858
- Cody McCowan isn't our killer

26:49.941 --> 26:51.359
because he was here
in our custody

26:51.443 --> 26:53.528
when Thomas was shot.
- Right.

26:53.611 --> 26:56.072
And our spree shooter
is still out there

26:56.156 --> 26:58.033
and still killing people.

26:58.116 --> 26:58.950
[dramatic music]

27:08.168 --> 27:11.046
- I was at my desk when
I heard the glass shatter.

27:11.129 --> 27:12.881
I jumped up right away,
but he got shot twice

27:12.964 --> 27:14.591
before I even knew
what happened.

27:14.674 --> 27:17.010
- So you didn't see anything?

27:17.093 --> 27:19.679
- I just looked down
and held him.

27:19.763 --> 27:23.224
Everything happened so fast.

27:23.308 --> 27:25.560
- Do you have any idea
who might be responsible?

27:25.643 --> 27:28.063
Any enemies or recent threats
on your father's life?

27:28.146 --> 27:31.900
- Not besides being detained
by you people.

27:31.983 --> 27:35.695
I mean, he had his detractors,
but not like this.

27:35.779 --> 27:38.198
All he ever wanted to do
was help people.

27:45.497 --> 27:48.750
- That mean anything to you?

27:48.833 --> 27:50.919
- That was from a protest march
last summer.

27:51.002 --> 27:52.879
That guy, Jack Powell,

27:52.962 --> 27:54.255
he cracked
Marcus Ervin's skull,

27:54.339 --> 27:57.092
knocked him out for two hours.

27:57.175 --> 27:58.718
Marcus was shot to death
last night.

27:58.802 --> 28:00.136
You think this is related?

28:00.220 --> 28:01.638
- Did your father
have anything to do

28:01.721 --> 28:03.098
with this Powell kid?
- Yeah.

28:03.181 --> 28:04.391
Marcus was poor.

28:04.474 --> 28:06.101
No one was speaking up for him,

28:06.184 --> 28:07.936
so my dad and I,
we lead the campaign

28:08.019 --> 28:09.604
to make sure the DA
prosecuted him

28:09.687 --> 28:11.106
for a hate crime,

28:11.189 --> 28:12.732
but Powell is in prison,
so what are you trying--

28:12.816 --> 28:15.360
- It's possible that one of his
accomplices is doing this,

28:15.443 --> 28:17.153
getting payback
for what happened.

28:17.237 --> 28:20.156
- Are you familiar with a group
called the Brooklyn Blockade?

28:20.240 --> 28:21.449
- No.
- Listen, Laila.

28:21.533 --> 28:24.244
If you and your dad both pushed
for this hate crime charge,

28:24.327 --> 28:26.454
there is a chance
you could be targeted too,

28:26.538 --> 28:28.331
so you really should lay low

28:28.415 --> 28:30.583
until we have this
under control.

28:30.667 --> 28:32.585
- So now
the sell-out's concerned

28:32.669 --> 28:34.087
about me and my family?

28:34.170 --> 28:36.631
[soft dramatic music]

28:36.714 --> 28:39.676
Ain't that sweet.

28:39.759 --> 28:41.845
- I'm sorry.
That's just out of line.

28:41.928 --> 28:43.596
We were there this morning
for a good reason.

28:43.680 --> 28:45.306
Your father threatened
Congressman Reed

28:45.390 --> 28:47.517
while carrying a gun.
- Scola, don't.

28:47.600 --> 28:48.768
- No, this is important.

28:48.852 --> 28:50.228
All we did was
follow the evidence.

28:50.311 --> 28:51.980
You don't have to like it,

28:52.063 --> 28:53.773
but that doesn't make
anyone here a sell-out.

28:53.857 --> 28:55.692
- Stuart.

28:55.775 --> 29:00.572
♪ ♪

29:00.655 --> 29:02.198
Please give us a call
if you think of anything

29:02.282 --> 29:03.658
that might be helpful.

29:03.741 --> 29:06.453
♪ ♪

29:06.536 --> 29:09.998
Listen, I know you're trying
to have my back,

29:10.081 --> 29:12.500
but don't speak for me again.

29:12.584 --> 29:16.713
I don't walk in your shoes.
You don't walk in mine.

29:16.796 --> 29:18.673
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

29:18.756 --> 29:20.675
I didn't realize.
- I know you didn't.

29:20.758 --> 29:23.178
But now you do.

29:23.261 --> 29:25.847
♪ ♪

29:25.930 --> 29:27.140
- Just talked to a witness.

29:27.223 --> 29:28.975
Saw an unmarked Crown Vic
flee the scene--

29:29.058 --> 29:31.519
New York plate.

29:31.603 --> 29:33.104
- Crown Vic.

29:34.772 --> 29:38.359
It's the same car
Cody McCowan drives.

29:38.443 --> 29:39.569
[door buzzes]

29:39.652 --> 29:41.529
- Looks like one of your
friends just borrowed your car.

29:41.613 --> 29:43.740
- And he used it
to kill Damian Thomas.

29:43.823 --> 29:46.493
- We're activists, not killers.
- Right.

29:46.576 --> 29:48.036
- Yeah,
that's right, activists.

29:48.119 --> 29:50.371
You know, white folks
can call theirselves that too.

29:50.455 --> 29:51.831
- Okay, well, your car
was spotted at the crime scene.

29:51.915 --> 29:53.541
We pulled this
from a security camera

29:53.625 --> 29:55.168
one block away.
That's your car, Cody.

29:55.251 --> 29:57.253
So why don't you tell us
who's driving it?

29:57.337 --> 29:59.380
- I don't know.
I can't see his face.

29:59.464 --> 30:01.216
Anybody could have taken
the damn thing.

30:01.299 --> 30:02.550
I keep the keys at the bar.

30:02.634 --> 30:04.010
For all I know,
someone stole it.

30:04.093 --> 30:06.888
- What about your .38?
The murder weapon was a .38.

30:06.971 --> 30:08.097
Who else has access
to your gun?

30:08.181 --> 30:11.684
- Nobody, my guns are locked up
in a safe in my apartment.

30:11.768 --> 30:13.311
♪ ♪

30:13.394 --> 30:15.605
What?

30:15.688 --> 30:18.900
- ERT searched McCowan's safe
after he was arrested.

30:18.983 --> 30:21.402
.38 wasn't in it.
- But McCowan didn't know that.

30:21.486 --> 30:23.279
- Which means someone took it
without his knowledge.

30:23.363 --> 30:25.240
- Hey, the only other prints
on Cody's gun safe

30:25.323 --> 30:27.075
just came back
to Janine McCowan.

30:27.158 --> 30:29.536
- Jack and Cody's mother.
We talked to her at the bar.

30:29.619 --> 30:30.828
- What do we know
about Janine?

30:30.912 --> 30:32.080
- 55 years old.

30:32.163 --> 30:34.332
Sole proprietor of Irish Haven
since 2006.

30:34.415 --> 30:37.252
Pays her taxes, pays her rent.
- She got a criminal history?

30:37.335 --> 30:38.628
- Nothing in the system.

30:38.711 --> 30:40.004
Only reason
she was fingerprinted

30:40.088 --> 30:41.422
was to get her liquor license.

30:41.506 --> 30:43.591
Seems like a regular,
law-abiding citizen.

30:43.675 --> 30:45.260
- Oh, yeah, until her baby boy
goes to prison

30:45.343 --> 30:48.263
and gets his head kicked in.
- Bring her in now.

30:48.346 --> 30:53.893
♪ ♪

30:53.977 --> 30:55.895
- FBI, nobody move!

30:55.979 --> 30:57.230
Show me your hands.

30:57.313 --> 30:59.107
- Federal agents.
Don't move!

30:59.190 --> 31:00.858
- Keep your hands up.
- Where's Janine McCowan?

31:00.942 --> 31:02.902
- I haven't seen her.

31:02.986 --> 31:05.113
- Where's your boss?
- I don't know.

31:05.196 --> 31:06.281
- When's the last time
you saw her?

31:06.364 --> 31:08.616
- I don't know, half hour ago?
- Did she say anything?

31:08.700 --> 31:09.784
- No, not a word--

31:09.867 --> 31:12.495
went straight to the back,
worked on her laptop for a bit,

31:12.579 --> 31:14.414
and then took off in a hurry.

31:14.497 --> 31:17.417
[dramatic music]

31:17.500 --> 31:20.420
[FBI agents chattering]

31:20.503 --> 31:22.797
♪ ♪

31:22.880 --> 31:25.300
- Go ahead of thunder.
Upstairs clear.

31:25.383 --> 31:26.593
[keyboard clacking]

31:26.676 --> 31:28.428
- Access denied.
- It's locked.

31:28.511 --> 31:30.763
- Maggie, look at this.

31:30.847 --> 31:32.807
Dated today, "Dear Cody,
I regret you were born

31:32.890 --> 31:35.435
into a world so full of hate."
- This a suicide note?

31:35.518 --> 31:37.562
- "The most hateful of all
are the hypocrite do-gooders

31:37.645 --> 31:39.355
"who destroyed our family.

31:39.439 --> 31:41.107
"They turned Jack
into a monster

31:41.190 --> 31:44.152
"for sport and for politics,
and he's braindead now.

31:44.235 --> 31:47.864
"Those responsible will pay.
I won't ever stop.

31:47.947 --> 31:50.491
"Forgive me for my sins,
but I didn't have a choice.

31:50.575 --> 31:53.202
I love you very much, Mom."

31:53.286 --> 31:56.497
- She's not done killing yet.
- No.

31:56.581 --> 31:58.875
♪ ♪

32:04.297 --> 32:05.173
- Clock's ticking, guys.

32:05.256 --> 32:06.591
Come on, we need
to find Janine McCowan now

32:06.674 --> 32:08.635
before she kills again.

32:08.718 --> 32:10.386
- Ian, got her computer.

32:10.470 --> 32:12.180
She was on it
before she left the bar.

32:12.263 --> 32:14.515
- All right.
- All right, all right.

32:14.599 --> 32:16.184
Let's get it done.
Find a way in.

32:16.267 --> 32:18.811
Everybody else, keep at it.
Let's find that Crown Vic.

32:18.895 --> 32:20.563
We tracking Janine's phone,
pulling PODs,

32:20.647 --> 32:22.065
surveillance cameras?
Let's go.

32:22.148 --> 32:23.524
- Any clue who
her next victim might be?

32:23.608 --> 32:24.525
- Nothing in
her good-bye letter,

32:24.609 --> 32:25.693
but I'm guessing it's connected

32:25.777 --> 32:26.861
to her son's arrest
or prosecution.

32:26.944 --> 32:28.029
- Yeah, we're putting
together a list--

32:28.112 --> 32:30.198
the DA who convicted Jack,
key witnesses.

32:30.281 --> 32:32.075
But what we really need
right now, Ian,

32:32.158 --> 32:33.451
is access to that laptop.

32:33.534 --> 32:35.536
- Two more seconds.
[computer beeps]

32:35.620 --> 32:36.287
Okay, I'm in.

32:36.371 --> 32:37.288
The last website Janine visited

32:37.372 --> 32:39.415
was a social media page
advertising a vigil

32:39.499 --> 32:41.584
for Damian Thomas.
- Where and when?

32:42.502 --> 32:44.879
- City Hall Park.
It starts in 20 minutes.

32:44.962 --> 32:46.881
- Now, guys,
this is a big event.

32:46.964 --> 32:49.717
NYPD's preparing for hundreds
of people to attend.

32:49.801 --> 32:53.054
- Which means hundreds
of potential targets.

32:53.137 --> 32:54.931
- Yeah.

32:55.014 --> 32:57.934
[dramatic music]

32:58.017 --> 33:00.561
♪ ♪

33:00.645 --> 33:02.689
- Rest in power, Damian.

33:04.816 --> 33:06.901
- She could be anywhere
in this crowd.

33:06.984 --> 33:09.362
- Peace, Damian Thomas.

33:09.445 --> 33:11.072
- All right,
we should split up.

33:11.155 --> 33:12.782
Let's stay connected
on the comms.

33:12.865 --> 33:13.908
- Hold on.

33:13.991 --> 33:16.077
- No justice, no peace!

33:16.160 --> 33:18.913
- We should get rid
of these jackets and vests.

33:18.996 --> 33:21.165
♪ ♪

33:21.249 --> 33:23.292
- Three people
have already been killed.

33:23.376 --> 33:26.254
- I get it, but these people
think that we're the enemy.

33:26.337 --> 33:27.588
We can get them all riled up

33:27.672 --> 33:31.092
and cause
an unnecessary commotion.

33:31.175 --> 33:33.761
- Makes sense to me.

33:33.845 --> 33:36.389
- Okay,
let's take off the vests.

33:36.472 --> 33:39.684
♪ ♪

33:39.767 --> 33:41.644
Hey, Jubal,
we've landed at the location.

33:41.728 --> 33:43.146
We don't have eyes
on our suspect.

33:43.229 --> 33:44.772
We'll keep you updated.

33:44.856 --> 33:48.568
♪ ♪

33:48.651 --> 33:50.445
- All right, we got boots
on the ground in Brooklyn,

33:50.528 --> 33:51.904
but still no eyes
on Janine McCowan.

33:51.988 --> 33:53.072
- I'm trying
to get street cam footage.

33:53.156 --> 33:54.073
Should have something
for you soon.

33:54.157 --> 33:56.325
- Got a hit on the BOLO.
- Yeah, where is it?

33:56.409 --> 33:57.577
- Cody McCowan's
Crown Vic is parked

33:57.660 --> 33:58.953
on the 100 block
at Church Street.

33:59.036 --> 34:00.163
NYPD says it's empty.

34:00.246 --> 34:02.081
- That's five blocks
from City Hall Park.

34:02.165 --> 34:03.291
- Yeah, what do we got, Ian?

34:03.374 --> 34:04.959
- There are street cameras
on both ends

34:05.042 --> 34:07.128
of that block.
- Great.

34:07.211 --> 34:13.176
♪ ♪

34:13.259 --> 34:14.218
- There by
the courtyard entrance.

34:14.302 --> 34:16.304
- Yeah, scrubbing back
to her leaving the car.

34:16.387 --> 34:18.556
♪ ♪

34:18.639 --> 34:21.809
- When was this?
- 11 minutes ago.

34:21.893 --> 34:24.187
- Guys, she exited the car
11 minutes ago

34:24.270 --> 34:25.563
on Church Street.

34:25.646 --> 34:27.565
We gotta assume she's heading
to City Hall Park

34:27.648 --> 34:29.442
from the west
on Chambers Street.

34:29.525 --> 34:30.485
She's wearing blue jeans,

34:30.568 --> 34:31.986
a dark hoodie
zipped to the neck,

34:32.069 --> 34:34.197
and her gun is
in a brown, leather handbag.

34:34.280 --> 34:36.532
- Jubal, can't find Janine
on any street cams in the area.

34:36.616 --> 34:38.159
- Just got word.

34:38.242 --> 34:39.327
We have a surveillance team
on site

34:39.410 --> 34:41.829
with eyes on the crowd.
- Beautiful.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.414
♪ ♪

34:43.498 --> 34:45.458
- Van at the corner
of Murray and Broadway.

34:45.541 --> 34:46.501
Got it.

34:46.584 --> 34:48.377
So DHS has a team on site
surveilling the vigil.

34:48.461 --> 34:50.671
They might have intel that can
help us find Janine McCowan.

34:50.755 --> 34:53.674
- You already know
how I feel about this.

34:53.758 --> 34:55.676
- And I get that,

34:55.760 --> 35:00.640
but Janine McCowan came here
to kill people, okay?

35:00.723 --> 35:02.809
Innocent people.

35:02.892 --> 35:06.354
♪ ♪

35:06.437 --> 35:08.147
- Okay.

35:09.565 --> 35:12.985
Okay, let's go.

35:13.069 --> 35:14.362
- Black time.

35:16.114 --> 35:17.615
- FBI, open up.

35:19.951 --> 35:22.203
[knocks]
FBI, open up now.

35:22.286 --> 35:24.914
Special Agent Tiffany Wallace,
FBI.

35:24.997 --> 35:26.707
We're looking
for an active shooter.

35:26.791 --> 35:28.042
- This is
an off-the-books operation.

35:28.125 --> 35:28.918
- We know.

35:29.001 --> 35:30.169
We just need you
to link up your feed

35:30.253 --> 35:31.754
to the Joint Operation Command.

35:35.675 --> 35:37.677
- Okay, but I need
to make a few calls first.

35:37.760 --> 35:39.428
- We don't have time
for phone calls.

35:39.512 --> 35:41.889
- Well, we can't share intel.

35:41.973 --> 35:43.266
- You can spy on Black people,

35:43.349 --> 35:46.561
but you can't help
save their lives?

35:46.644 --> 35:50.398
You really want
to stake your career on that?

35:50.481 --> 35:52.900
- Okay, we'll get the feed
to the JOC.

35:52.984 --> 35:56.237
♪ ♪

35:56.320 --> 35:57.446
- We're all synced up
with the DHS feed.

35:57.530 --> 36:00.533
That is live spy cam footage
of the Damian Thomas vigil.

36:00.616 --> 36:02.410
- Janine McCowan
is in here somewhere.

36:02.493 --> 36:05.371
The question is where.

36:05.454 --> 36:07.748
- The abandoned Crown Vic,
is that visible on this screen?

36:07.832 --> 36:09.375
- Right, 100 Church.

36:09.458 --> 36:10.918
Okay, where is it?
There.

36:11.002 --> 36:12.837
Okay, Ian, we need
to roll back this footage

36:12.920 --> 36:16.424
to the exact moment
Janine left her car.

36:16.507 --> 36:17.633
- Okay, there.

36:17.717 --> 36:18.801
Can we track her movements
from there?

36:18.885 --> 36:21.721
- Oh, yeah,
adding a tracer now.

36:21.804 --> 36:23.264
- Good, good, good.

36:23.347 --> 36:24.724
Okay, here we go.

36:24.807 --> 36:26.392
Where's she going?
Where's she going?

36:26.475 --> 36:27.852
Okay, okay.

36:32.190 --> 36:37.445
♪ ♪

36:37.528 --> 36:38.988
She ducked
into that storefront.

36:39.071 --> 36:40.781
What then?

36:40.865 --> 36:43.117
- This is real time.
She's still in there.

36:43.201 --> 36:45.620
- Get me an address!
- Address is 275 Broadway.

36:45.703 --> 36:47.288
It's a hardware store
that closed at 5:00 p.m.

36:47.371 --> 36:48.539
- Okay, I'm pulling up
live street cam view

36:48.623 --> 36:49.624
of that address.

36:49.707 --> 36:51.959
- Yeah, yeah, guys,
she's hiding in the entryway

36:52.043 --> 36:56.631
of 275 Broadway,
west edge of the park.

36:56.714 --> 36:58.466
- We're moving in now.

36:58.549 --> 37:02.970
♪ ♪

37:03.054 --> 37:04.597
Jubal, she's not here.

37:08.225 --> 37:09.810
- Wait, how long
is the delay on this?

37:09.894 --> 37:11.646
- Can't be more than
ten seconds.

37:11.729 --> 37:12.939
- Guys, you just missed her.

37:13.022 --> 37:14.815
She's heading east
toward the park.

37:14.899 --> 37:19.153
♪ ♪

37:19.236 --> 37:21.280
- There she is
in the tan jacket.

37:21.364 --> 37:22.990
- Copy that,
we've got eyes on her.

37:23.074 --> 37:24.033
- All right,
you go around left.

37:24.116 --> 37:26.035
I'll stay with Janine.
- Yeah.

37:26.118 --> 37:33.167
♪ ♪

37:33.668 --> 37:35.670
- Thank you all
for coming out tonight

37:35.753 --> 37:37.630
to celebrate my father's life.

37:37.713 --> 37:40.508
Damian Thomas was never a man
who sat back

37:40.591 --> 37:43.844
and just accepted
the way things were.

37:43.928 --> 37:47.682
He believed that change
was possible without violence!

37:47.765 --> 37:49.725
From an early age,
my father decided

37:49.809 --> 37:53.104
that as long as he had
a point of view and a voice,

37:53.187 --> 37:55.189
both his point of view
and his voice

37:55.272 --> 37:56.857
were going to be heard.

37:56.941 --> 37:59.568
Tonight, we honor his legacy

37:59.652 --> 38:01.821
by gathering together
peacefully.

38:01.904 --> 38:05.992
The cycle of violence
stops now!

38:06.075 --> 38:08.202
Tonight!

38:08.286 --> 38:10.037
It ends with us!

38:10.121 --> 38:13.165
[cheers and applause]

38:15.793 --> 38:18.921
- FBI, drop your weapon!

38:19.005 --> 38:20.589
- [grunts]

38:20.673 --> 38:23.259
[crowd clamoring]

38:24.844 --> 38:27.013
- It's over, Janine.

38:27.096 --> 38:29.056
You're under arrest for murder.

38:29.140 --> 38:36.147
♪ ♪

38:42.778 --> 38:44.280
- Thank you.

38:44.363 --> 38:51.245
♪ ♪

38:51.328 --> 38:55.875
- We got the shooter,
saved a life maybe two.

38:55.958 --> 38:57.376
- Yeah.

38:59.378 --> 39:01.797
I know.
I'm supposed to feel good.

39:04.675 --> 39:07.970
What DHS was doing was wrong...

39:08.054 --> 39:10.181
in my book at least, and...

39:11.849 --> 39:14.393
I still went over there,
and I used their information.

39:14.477 --> 39:17.980
- We still ran over there
and used the information.

39:18.064 --> 39:19.815
- Yeah.

39:20.900 --> 39:22.693
We didn't have a choice.

39:24.528 --> 39:26.572
But that is such crap...

39:26.655 --> 39:28.949
[soft dramatic music]

39:29.033 --> 39:32.828
'Cause we do...have a choice.

39:32.912 --> 39:34.955
♪ ♪

39:35.039 --> 39:38.417
And today we chose to do
what was convenient.

39:42.046 --> 39:44.048
I guess what I mean is that...

39:45.549 --> 39:46.634
You don't get to pick
and choose

39:46.717 --> 39:50.429
when to have integrity...

39:50.513 --> 39:53.641
when to stand up
for what's right, you know?

39:53.724 --> 40:00.147
♪ ♪

40:00.231 --> 40:03.776
When to be the kind
of Black woman you want to be.

40:06.737 --> 40:10.032
- Look, I get it.

40:10.116 --> 40:13.994
I do.

40:14.078 --> 40:18.415
And the truth is that sometimes
there's a cost to victory...

40:18.499 --> 40:21.836
♪ ♪

40:21.919 --> 40:24.296
But that doesn't mean
that it's not a victory.
